          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-1199 build : Pass in the configure arguments to rpmbuild.",
        "message": "LU-1199 build : Pass in the configure arguments to rpmbuild.\n\nCurrently the rpm spec file for lustre and ldiskfs parses\nthe configure arguments inside the rpm spec file instead\nof the more traditional way of passing arguments with\nrpmbuild. This patch is the first step to doing this by\nparsing the configure options in the Makefile and then\ncalling rpmbuild in the Makefile with rpmbuild options\nwhich the spec file can act upon. This patch as a first\nstep converts the kernel source and object options of\nconfigure into rpmbuild options and uses them in the\nspec file.\n\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\nChange-Id: I49e8b3b9fcd8edc52f93075032da96e248b1056f\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
